The elder Shriver discovered the bodies Carey and Valerie after getting a call from Martha around 10.30pm but couldn't immediately find their 13-year-old child, according to the Kansas City Star.

The boy, who hadn't woken up, was later found in his bed and taken in by his relative. 

He said that Aldridge 'didn't have much to do with people' and 'kind of stayed to himself'.

